{{multiple issues| {{notability|date=February 2017}} {{one source|date=February 2017}} {{third-party|date=February 2017}} }} {{Infobox journal | title = Anales de la Universidad de Chile | cover = | editor = Jennifer Abate Cruces | language = Spanish | discipline = [[Arts]], [[humanities]], [[science]] | abbreviation = An. Univ. Chile | publisher = [[University of Chile]] | country = Chile | frequency = Biannual | history = 1843-present | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://anales.uchile.cl/ | link1 = http://anales.uchile.cl/index.php/ANUC/issue/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://anales.uchile.cl/index.php/ANUC/issue/archive | link2-name = Online archive | CODEN = AUCHA3 | LCCN = 55037211 | eISSN = 0717-8883 | ISSN = 0365-7779 | OCLC = 889512243 }} '''''Anales de la Universidad de Chile''''' is a biannual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] containing research and critical reflections on [[art]]s, [[humanities]], and [[science]]. It was established in 1843 and is published by the [[University of Chile]]. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Jennifer Abate Cruces (University of Chile).
