{{orphan|date=January 2012}}
'''Arthur Th. Witteveen''' (born 19??) is a Dutch judge and legal writer. He is the First Secretary of the [[International Court of Justice]] in [[The Hague]].<ref>[http://www.icj-cij.org/presscom/index.php?pr=99&pt=1&p1=6&p2=1&PHPSESSID=5c407 www.icj-cij.org]</ref> In April 1996 he published a book on ''The International Court of Justice 1946-1996'' with [[Arthur Eyffinger]]. Witteveen practiced [[Chinese calligraphy]] throughout his life, obtaining a 9th dan,  and after his retirement as secretary he studied [[Sinology]] at [[Leiden University]]. In 2002 he wrote ''De dans van het penseel. Een korte inleiding tot de Chinese Calligrafie'' ("The Dance of the Brush: A Short Introduction to Chinese Calligraphy").<ref>[http://magazine.sieboldhuis.org/custom/PDF/TNJR_v1_1_2010_Witteveen_Calligrafie.pdf Short bio]</ref>

