{{italic title}}
'''''End of the Past''''' is a book by Pakistani journalist, cultural critic and satirist [[Nadeem Farooq Paracha|Nadeem F. Paracha]]. Published by Vanguard Publications in 2016, it is a social history of Pakistan in which Paracha charts the religious and cultural evolution of Pakistan through the country's cultural, sporting and ideological histories.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Report|first1=Dawn|title=End of the past: Culture critic NFP’s first book published|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1235941|website=Dawn.Com|publisher=Vanguard|accessdate=8 Feb 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = End of the Past: Story of What Went Wrong With Pakistan|url = http://www.huffingtonpost.com/raza-habib-raja/what-went-wrong-with-paki_b_11712170.html|website = Huffington Post|access-date = 2017-02-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = End of the Past|url = http://www.thefridaytimes.com/tft/end-of-the-past/|website = Friday Times|access-date = 2017-02-21}}</ref> 

